File Management Systems(FMS)
==============================
A file management system is a system where data is stored in files on the operating systems. each application 
program must handled its own storage data. retrieval and updating , File systems can be provided by the 
local operating systems.

File systems are best suitable for to store very less amount of information.
ex: A Library Management System Storing Books in a separate text files like books.txt, members.txt

Limitations of File Management Systems
========================================
1.Ôüá ÔüáData Redundancy : same data is stored in multiple files.
2.Ôüá ÔüáData Inconsistency : updates in one file may not be reflected in another.
3.Ôüá Ôüápoor data security : no proper accessed control
4.Ôüá ÔüáDifficult Data Retrieval : searching requires custom programs.
5.Ôüá ÔüáIntegrity Issues : No Constraints(ex: roll numbers uniqueness)
6.Ôüá Ôüáscalability issues : hard to manage as data grows.
to overcome the above problems in File systems we should go for databases.

Database Management System (DBMS)
====================================
A DBMS is a collection of programs that enables to users to create, manage and manipulate databases.

it acts as an interface between user and database.

Advantages of DBMS
====================
1.Ôüá ÔüáWe can store huge amount of information in databases.
2.Ôüá ÔüáQuery language support is available for every databases and hence we perform database operations easily
3.Ôüá Ôüáto access data present in the databases . compulsory username and password must be required hence data is secured.
4.Ôüá Ôüáinside database data will be stored in the form of tables. while developing databases table schemas, database admin 
follows various constraints like unique key, Primary key, Foreign key.. etc while prevent data duplication. hence there 
is no chance off data inconsistency problems

Limitations of Databases
=============================
1.Ôüá ÔüáDatabases cannot store huge amount of information like (TB)
2.Ôüá Ôüádatabases can provide supports for only structured data(tabular data or relational data) and cannot provide supports for 
unstructured data or semi- structured data (likes videos ,audios, xml data).

To overcome these problems we should go for some more advanced databases like data warehouses, big data.. etc.

